      <section eId="sec_48_8_1">
        <num>48-8-1</num>
        <content>
          <p>It is the intention of the General Assembly in enacting this article to exercise its full and complete power to tax the retail purchase, retail sale, rental, storage, use, and consumption of tangible personal property and the services described in this article except to the extent prohibited by the Constitutions of the United States and of this state and except to the extent of specific exemptions provided in this article.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1951, p. 360, § 4; Ga. L. 1965, p. 13, § 2; Code 1933, § 91A-4506, enacted by Ga. L. 1978, p. 309, § 2; Ga. L. 1979, p. 5, § 93.)</p>
        </content>
      </section>
